{"v":1,"id":"AxBDyW8ZLuIpVzINLTjH","createdAt":"2026-06-23T03:06:11.037Z","app":{"name":"AxiVale","version":"1.3.1"},"kind":"conversation","title":"Compare all the players who have played Reaper across all available runs. Use only metrics from time logged on Reaper. Compare only players who are members of FAFO guild. Prioritize Downs Contribution > Strips > Damage to Downs > Damage Per Second > Outgoing Conditions > Outgoing CC. Player downs and deaths count as minimum negative. Minimum Sample of 2 runs per player. Created a table with weighted results","turns":[{"userText":"Compare all the players who have played Reaper across all available runs. Use only metrics from time logged on Reaper. Compare only players who are members of FAFO guild. Prioritize Downs Contribution > Strips > Damage to Downs > Damage Per Second > Outgoing Conditions > Outgoing CC. Player downs and deaths count as minimum negative. Minimum Sample of 2 runs per player. Created a table with weighted results","agentText":"\n\nI’m pulling the FAFO roster and the AxiBridge rollup first so I can filter to guild members, isolate Reaper-only rows, and then rank them on the metrics you specified.\n\nThe rollup row confirms AxiBridge tracks per-account profession breakdown, but not yet whether the damage/downs fields are already split by profession in that rollup. I’m checking the FAFO roster and the player-stats shape next so I can avoid mixing non-Reaper time into the comparison.\n\n`gw2_guild_members` rejected the tag lookup, so I’m retrying with FAFO’s exact guild id from the API key and inspecting a real run summary to see where the per-run Reaper metrics live.\n\nI have the full FAFO roster and the run index now. Next step is aggregating every Reaper appearance across all 30 runs so I can filter to members with at least two Reaper runs and score them consistently.\n\nI’ve narrowed the pool to FAFO members with at least two Reaper runs. I’m switching the ranking to per-run averages so volume of attendance doesn’t swamp the comparison, then I’ll weight by your priority order and apply only light penalties for player downs/deaths.\n\nThe candidate list is stable now. I’m doing one last check on whether AxiBridge exposes outgoing conditions and outgoing CC at the same Reaper-only cross-run grain; if not, I’ll keep the weighting strict to the metrics that are actually available without contaminating it with non-Reaper time.\n\nMes.1906 ranks first among FAFO Reapers with a weighted score of 224 across 3 Reaper runs.\n\nI compared all 30 available runs from 2026-04-24 through 2026-06-21, filtered to FAFO guild members only, then kept only players with at least 2 runs logged on Reaper. To avoid attendance volume dominating the result, the table uses per-run averages. Weighted score uses rank points with your priority order and only light survival penalties: `6x avg Down Contribution + 5x avg Strips + 4x avg Damage/run + 1x low Downs taken + 1x low Deaths`. I did not inject whole-account DPS / condition / outgoing CC numbers, because that would mix in non-Reaper time.\n\n| Rank | Account | Reaper Runs | Weighted Score | Avg Down Contribution | Avg Strips | Avg Damage/Run | Avg Downs Taken | Avg Deaths |\n|---|---|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|---:|\n| 1 | Mes.1906 | 3 | 224 | 1,572,278 | 1,340.7 | 8,384,123 | 6.3 | 4.0 |\n| 2 | Aeri.4529 | 7 | 198 | 1,358,347 | 1,277.4 | 7,763,205 | 12.7 | 8.6 |\n| 3 | FatherHyperion.1047 | 6 | 195 | 792,781 | 1,534.0 | 7,260,929 | 3.8 | 2.8 |\n| 4 | iNicooo.9587 | 7 | 188 | 1,096,939 | 1,195.6 | 6,594,092 | 6.4 | 4.4 |\n| 5 | Hostile Pudding.5617 | 11 | 164 | 962,113 | 1,166.0 | 5,903,898 | 10.0 | 5.3 |\n| 6 | Athena.4562 | 9 | 143 | 733,164 | 1,129.0 | 4,565,913 | 7.6 | 3.2 |\n| 7 | Siren.9741 | 5 | 132 | 711,027 | 1,022.8 | 6,189,993 | 10.2 | 6.0 |\n| 8 | Astronauta.1087 | 3 | 118 | 694,005 | 809.3 | 4,016,646 | 4.0 | 1.7 |\n| 9 | Blades Of Fatalis.1279 | 4 | 109 | 824,285 | 498.3 | 4,094,712 | 12.8 | 8.8 |\n| 10 | Zikum.4126 | 2 | 82 | 543,148 | 378.0 | 3,113,756 | 3.0 | 0.5 |\n| 11 | Endless.4325 | 10 | 73 | 456,376 | 620.4 | 3,525,013 | 16.3 | 11.1 |\n| 12 | Kurayamino.9738 | 5 | 62 | 341,318 | 725.4 | 3,053,580 | 19.4 | 11.4 |\n| 13 | brittikaye.6159 | 13 | 54 | 303,001 | 501.1 | 2,448,580 | 9.1 | 4.8 |\n| 14 | Pentheus.4571 | 2 | 43 | 41,588 | 30.0 | 298,437 | 0.0 | 0.0 |\n\nKey read:\n- `Mes.1906` wins on raw kill pressure: best average down contribution, best average damage/run, and 2nd-best strips.\n- `FatherHyperion.1047` lands 3rd overall because strips and survivability pull him above `iNicooo.9587`, even with lower down contribution.\n- `Aeri.4529` has elite offensive output, but the light downs/deaths penalty keeps him just behind `Mes.1906`.\n- `Pentheus.4571` had the cleanest survival line, but the weighted model correctly leaves him last because the offensive Reaper output is far below the rest.\n\nNo runs were reported stale in the data I used. If you want, I can do a second pass that splits this into:\n1. pure offensive rank only, or\n2. recent-form rank for just June runs.","filedAt":"6:27 PM","tools":[{"name":"gw2_account_info"},{"name":"axibridge_query","display":{"kind":"code","data":{"title":"Query result","text":"{\n  \"account\": \"Bouzouki.7598\",\n  \"characterNames\": [\n    \"Extra Pickle\",\n    \"Fallen Pickle\"\n  ],\n  \"profession\": \"Specter\",\n  \"professionBreakdown\": [\n    {\n      \"profession\": \"Specter\",\n      \"runs\": 6\n    },\n    {\n      \"profession\": \"Scourge\",\n      \"runs\": 1\n    }\n  ],\n  \"runs\": 7,\n  \"combatTimeMs\": 20047181,\n  \"squadTimeMs\": 46074520,\n  \"lastSeenTs\": 1782089340000\n}"}}},{"name":"axibridge_query","display":{"kind":"code","data":{"title":"Query result","text":"[\n  \"account\",\n  \"characterNames\",\n  \"profession\",\n  \"professionBreakdown\",\n  \"runs\",\n  \"combatTimeMs\",\n  \"squadTimeMs\",\n  \"lastSeenTs\"\n]"}}},{"name":"axibridge_player_stats","display":{"kind":"table","data":{"title